As a fast-growing IT solution company, we are looking for a Software Cyber Security Engineer to join our in-house development team. As a Software Cyber Security Engineer, you will be mainly in charge of the security operations of IT systems in security design, security risk assessment, and security operations management, and work closely with developers to ensure highest quality product delivery. This role offers the skills and experience required to proceed further in IT industry.

Responsibilities:
 Conduct system security review to ensure necessary security measures and standards required are incorporated into the system developed by our programmer team;
 Design, develop and implement innovative software protection solutions to counter cyber threats;
 Conduct penetration test for web and mobile applications and author penetration test reports with professional documentation of identified and exploited vulnerabilities/
weaknesses and provide detailed remediation guidance for findings;
 Adapt industry security guidelines such as CIS Benchmark, GDPR or checklists available from PDPC. Where applicable customize these benchmarks to align with our system;
 Investigate and analyze security incidents to refine existing software security strategies and solutions;
 Identify emerging technology issues including security trends, vulnerabilities and threats
 Collaborate with development team to improve overall product quality;

Requirement:
 Degree in Infocomm Security, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Information Technology or equivalent
 Minimum of two years direct Cyber Security experience in a security analyst, engineer, architect, consultant or a similar role
 Minimum of one year of experience in software penetration testing
 Knowledge of Cyber Security Laws, Personal Data Protection Act
 Working knowledge of all vulnerability classes on the OWASP Periodic Table of Vulnerabilities.
 Solid knowledge of all web technologies, especially web services, web applications, Service Oriented Architectures, and network/web protocols
 Certified Information Security Systems Security Professional (CISSP) or GSEC will be advantageous
 Good attitude, responsible and proactive

If you would like to apply for this position, please kindly email your CV to us at tony@dlideas.com

Please include the below information in your resume:
 Current &amp; Expected salary
 Reason(s) for leaving
 Availability to commence work